prompt:
Add a public generic class called Repository to Generic.calr with a type constraint requiring T to be a class (reference type).

Use this exact Calor type constraint syntax:
§CL{c001:Repository:pub}<T>
  §WHERE T : class
  §FLD{List<T>:_items:priv}
  §MT{m001:Add:pub}
    §I{T:item}
    §O{void}
    §PUSH{_items} item
  §/MT{m001}
§/CL{c001}

The §WHERE T : constraint syntax adds type constraints:
- class - T must be a reference type
- struct - T must be a value type
- new() - T must have a parameterless constructor
- IInterface - T must implement the interface
